ground to fight
back.

24:27.366 --> 24:32.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Jane
Ferguson reports
from Irbil and the Nineveh Plain
in Northern

24:32.838 --> 24:34.606 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Iraq.

24:34.640 --> 24:41.980 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Iraqi Christians
celebrate
Easter's Holy Week, a time of
rebirth, hope,

24:42.014 --> 24:46.952 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
salvation. But many here see
little hope in
their ancestral lands. They have
fled ISIS'

24:46.985 --> 24:53.158 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
grip for the nearby safety of
Irbil city,
and they have no idea if they
can ever go

24:53.192 --> 24:55.227 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
home.

24:55.260 --> 25:00.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Father Douglas Bazi has worked
to raise awareness
around the world of the plight
of Iraq's Christians.

25:01.033 --> 25:06.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yet even he understands why most
choose to
leave a nation they struggle to
feel a part

25:06.071 --> 25:07.873 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of.

25:07.906 --> 25:11.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FATHER DOUGLAS BAZI, Iraq: The
bigger problem
here is when the Christians
feeling that we

25:11.210 --> 25:20.853 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are not belong to this land
again -- anymore.
Without -- with this feeling, I
am not feeling

25:20.886 --> 25:26.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that I belong to Iraq. So, why I
am here?
Why should I be target every
time?

25:26.959 --> 25:33.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And don't -- please, don't blame
my people
when they, because always they
say, oh, it's

25:33.699 --> 25:40.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a shame, the Middle East without
-- without
Christians. It's really a shame.
The Christians,

25:40.339 --> 25:42.107 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
they are leaving.

25:42.141 --> 25:47.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, why you put shame on my
people? Why not
put shame to those actually
force people to

25:47.746 --> 25:49.481 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
leave?

25:49.515 --> 25:52.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: The number of
Christians in
the Middle East has fallen from
14 percent

25:52.851 --> 26:02.928 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
