percent in
2010. Before 2003, there were
around 1.5 million

26:02.961 --> 26:09.168 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Christians in Iraq. Now it is
believed less
than 200,000 remain.

26:09.201 --> 26:13.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And many of those have been
displaced from
their villages by the Islamic
State. These

26:13.906 --> 26:18.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Christians fled their town as
ISIS fighters
approached, losing everything
they have ever

26:19.011 --> 26:22.681 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
known in just a few terrifying
hours.

26:22.714 --> 26:28.454 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now they live in Father Douglas'
church yard.
They cannot go home, but they
have nowhere

26:28.487 --> 26:34.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
else to go. Compared to many
refugees in this
war, they are lucky. The global
Christian

26:34.726 --> 26:39.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
community is supporting them,
and some have
been offered new lives in
Europe.

26:39.765 --> 26:45.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Hekmat Peter doesn't just
want to go home.
He wants to go back in time, to
when neighbors

26:45.904 --> 26:47.673 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
lived in harmony.

26:47.706 --> 26:52.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HEKMAT PETER, Iraq (through
translator): We
don't want a place for Christian
people only,

26:52.511 --> 26:58.884 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but like we used to live. Our
town was surrounded
by 30 villages of Muslims. So we
want to live

26:58.917 --> 27:02.921 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
together in peace, like we did
for many years.

27:02.955 --> 27:09.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Fighting back
will not solve
the problem either, says Father
Douglas. He

27:09.161 --> 27:13.832 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
