Christians should
never take up arms against their
attackers.

27:13.866 --> 27:19.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FATHER DOUGLAS BAZI: We don't
believe in war
at all. We don't believe that
the rights should

27:19.771 --> 27:26.245 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
be taken by weapon. And,
actually, as a Christian,
we don't have militia belong to
the Christian.

27:26.278 --> 27:29.181 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, as a Christian, we don't
have a militia.

27:29.214 --> 27:34.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those people, if they want to go
to the military
and to serve there and be paid,
this is their

27:34.686 --> 27:39.858 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
choice. We are never giving a
blessing to
war.

27:39.892 --> 27:46.532 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JANE FERGUSON: These men
disagree. They are
Christians who have come
together into a small

27:46.565 --> 27:51.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
